italian-accented-words

By Alessandro Cantini

List of substitutions of Italian accented words

italian
languages
accents

Paste this command in a terminal to install the package

espanso install italian-accented-words
Description
Source
This package contains a list of accented Italian words substitutions. It only contains words which don't have a non-accented corresponding word in the Italian dictionary. For example 'scherz' is not present since 'scherzo' is also a valid Italian word, while 'citt' is present because 'citta' is not an Italian word.
Some words are extracted from verb-data which is distributed under CC BY-SA 3.0 licence.
